# Supabase — used by the Pipeline CSV importer (app/api/pipeline/upload).
# SERVER-SIDE ONLY. The service role key bypasses Row Level Security, so it must
# never be exposed to the browser (do NOT prefix it with NEXT_PUBLIC_).
#
# Find these in: Supabase dashboard → Project Settings → API.
# Copy this file to `.env.local` and fill in the values, then restart `next dev`.
#
# If these are left unset, the Pipeline tool runs in DEMO mode: it parses the CSV
# and animates the flow but simulates the write instead of hitting Supabase.

# This is a TEMPLATE. Never paste real keys here — only into .env.local (gitignored).
SUPABASE_URL=https://YOUR_PROJECT_REF.supabase.co
SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY=your-service-role-key-here

# ── Send Campaigns (Automation) — Pipeline → Send Campaigns tab ──
# The n8n webhook that delivers the outreach emails. The tab POSTs the rendered,
# per-lead messages here ({ campaign, messages: [{ to, subject, html, leadId }] }).
# Point it at a Webhook-trigger node fronting the "Send a message" Gmail node in
# references/Leadgen Automation.json. If unset, sends run in DEMO mode (simulated,
# nothing delivered) — exactly like the importer without Supabase creds.
# N8N_CAMPAIGN_WEBHOOK_URL=https://your-n8n.example.com/webhook/apmg-campaign

# ── Sector attachment PDF compression (Sector Playbooks tab) ──
# Attachment PDFs over ~18 MB are auto-compressed with Ghostscript on upload so
# they clear the n8n Gmail node's ~25 MB attachment cap (see lib/pipeline/pdfCompress).
# This REQUIRES the Ghostscript binary on the host: `gs` on Linux/macOS,
# `gswin64c`/`gswin32c` on Windows (Docker: `apt-get install -y ghostscript`).
# Without it, large PDFs are stored uncompressed and the UI warns they may be too
# big for Gmail. Set this only if the binary isn't on PATH / has a custom name.
# GHOSTSCRIPT_BIN=/usr/bin/gs

# Public base URL the tracked CTA links point at, e.g. /t/<lead>?c=<campaign>
# (see app/t/[id]/route.ts). Optional — defaults to the request origin. Set this
# to your deployed domain so links in emails resolve correctly. Safe to expose
# (NEXT_PUBLIC_), it's only a hostname. NOTE: NEXT_PUBLIC_ vars are baked at
# BUILD time — after changing this in Vercel you must redeploy for it to take.
# Use the apex, or a dedicated subdomain (app.apmgmaintenance.com.au) if the
# apex will host a marketing site.
# NEXT_PUBLIC_TRACK_BASE=https://apmgmaintenance.com.au

# ── Portal chat bubble (public /portal) ──
# A SECOND Anthropic key for the customer-facing chat bubble
# (app/api/portal/chat → lib/ai/portalChat.ts). It answers visitor questions
# grounded ONLY in the knowledge base (components/knowledgebase/business.md),
# using claude-haiku-4-5. Keep it DISTINCT from ANTHROPIC_API_KEY: the chat
# endpoint is public and anonymous, so its spend is walled off from the outreach
# composer's quota — public abuse can never starve campaign drafting. The route
# is additionally protected by a per-IP rate limit, input/turn caps, a same-
# origin (CSRF) floor, and a KB-only system prompt that refuses off-topic and
# jailbreak use. If unset, the bubble still renders and degrades to an "enquire
# instead" nudge rather than erroring.
# PORTAL_CHAT_ANTHROPIC_KEY=sk-ant-...
